truthful /ˈtruːθfʊl/

1. ADJ If a person or their comments are truthful , they are honest and do not tell any lies. 诚实的 

例： Most religions teach you to be truthful. 大多数宗教都教你要诚实。 

例： We've all learned to be fairly truthful about our personal lives. 我们都已学会了对我们的个人生活要相当诚实。 

2. truthfully ADV 诚实地 [ADV with v] 

例： I answered all their questions truthfully. 我如实地回答了他们的所有问题。

